Properties.Name: activityadditionalparams
Properties.Description: For internal use only.

Properties.Name: activityid
Properties.Description: Unique identifier of the phone call activity.

Properties.Name: activitytypecode
Properties.Description: Shows the type of activity.

Properties.Name: actualdurationminutes
Properties.Description: Type the number of minutes spent on the phone call. The duration is used in reporting.

Properties.Name: actualend
Properties.Description: Enter the actual end date and time of the phone call. By default, it displays the date and time when the activity was completed or canceled, but can be edited to capture the actual duration of the phone call.

Properties.Name: actualstart
Properties.Description: Enter the actual start date and time for the phone call. By default, it displays the date and time when the activity was created, but can be edited to capture the actual duration of the phone call.

Properties.Name: category
Properties.Description: Type a category to identify the phone call type, such as lead gathering or customer follow-up, to tie the phone call to a business group or function.

Properties.Name: createdby
Properties.Description: Shows who created the record.

Properties.Name: createdon
Properties.Description: Shows the date and time when the record was created. The date and time are displayed in the time zone selected in Microsoft Dynamics 365 options.

Properties.Name: createdonbehalfby
Properties.Description: Shows who created the record on behalf of another user.

Properties.Name: description
Properties.Description: Type additional information to describe the phone call, such as the primary message or the products and services discussed.

Properties.Name: directioncode
Properties.Description: Select the direction of the phone call as incoming or outbound.

Properties.Name: dt_calltype
Properties.Description:
Orignating Sales
  * An orignating call to a customer or a prospect with the purpose of generating a sales
Customer Service
  * A call dealing with order details
  * clarifying order quantites or art

Properties.Name: exchangerate
Properties.Description: Shows the conversion rate of the record's currency. The exchange rate is used to convert all money fields in the record from the local currency to the system's default currency.

Properties.Name: from
Properties.Description: Enter the account, contact, lead, or user who made the phone call.

Properties.Name: importsequencenumber
Properties.Description: Unique identifier of the data import or data migration that created this record.

Properties.Name: isbilled
Properties.Description: Information which specifies whether the phone call activity was billed as part of resolving a case.

Properties.Name: isregularactivity
Properties.Description: Information regarding whether the activity is a regular activity type or event type.

Properties.Name: isworkflowcreated
Properties.Description: Indication which specifies if the phone call activity was created by a workflow rule.

Properties.Name: lastonholdtime
Properties.Description: Contains the date and time stamp of the last on hold time.

Properties.Name: leftvoicemail
Properties.Description: Select whether a voice mail was left for the person.

Properties.Name: modifiedby
Properties.Description: Shows who last updated the record.

Properties.Name: modifiedon
Properties.Description: Shows the date and time when the record was last updated. The date and time are displayed in the time zone selected in Microsoft Dynamics 365 options.

Properties.Name: modifiedonbehalfby
Properties.Description: Shows who last updated the record on behalf of another user.

Properties.Name: msdyncrm_associatedcustomerjourneyiteration
Properties.Description: Customer journey iteration

Properties.Name: onholdtime
Properties.Description: Shows how long, in minutes, that the record was on hold.

Properties.Name: overriddencreatedon
Properties.Description: Date and time that the record was migrated.

Properties.Name: ownerid
Properties.Description: Enter the user or team who is assigned to manage the record. This field is updated every time the record is assigned to a different user.

Properties.Name: owningbusinessunit
Properties.Description: Unique identifier of the business unit that owns the phone call activity.

Properties.Name: owningteam
Properties.Description: Unique identifier of the team that owns the phone call activity.

Properties.Name: owninguser
Properties.Description: Unique identifier of the user that owns the phone call activity.

Properties.Name: phonenumber
Properties.Description: Type the phone number.

Properties.Name: prioritycode
Properties.Description: Select the priority so that preferred customers or critical issues are handled quickly.

Properties.Name: processid
Properties.Description: Shows the ID of the process.

Properties.Name: rc_callduration
Properties.Description: Custom field for call duraction

Properties.Name: rc_callrecording
Properties.Description: Custom field for call recording

Properties.Name: rc_callstatus
Properties.Description: Custom field for call status

Properties.Name: regardingobjectid
Properties.Description: Choose the record that the phone call relates to.

Properties.Name: scheduleddurationminutes
Properties.Description: Scheduled duration of the phone call activity, specified in minutes.

Properties.Name: scheduledend
Properties.Description: Enter the expected due date and time.

Properties.Name: scheduledstart
Properties.Description: Enter the expected due date and time.

Properties.Name: serviceid
Properties.Description: Unique identifier for an associated service.

Properties.Name: slaid
Properties.Description: Choose the service level agreement (SLA) that you want to apply to the Phone Call record.

Properties.Name: slainvokedid
Properties.Description: Last SLA that was applied to this Phone Call. This field is for internal use only.

Properties.Name: sortdate
Properties.Description: Shows the date and time by which the activities are sorted.

Properties.Name: stageid
Properties.Description: Shows the ID of the stage.

Properties.Name: statecode
Properties.Description: Shows whether the phone call is open, completed, or canceled. Completed and canceled phone calls are read-only and can't be edited.

Properties.Name: statuscode
Properties.Description: Select the phone call's status.

Properties.Name: subcategory
Properties.Description: Type a subcategory to identify the phone call type and relate the activity to a specific product, sales region, business group, or other function.

Properties.Name: subject
Properties.Description: Type a short description about the objective or primary topic of the phone call.

Properties.Name: subscriptionid
Properties.Description: For internal use only.

Properties.Name: timezoneruleversionnumber
Properties.Description: For internal use only.

Properties.Name: to
Properties.Description: Enter the account, contact, lead, or user recipients of the phone call.

Properties.Name: transactioncurrencyid
Properties.Description: Choose the local currency for the record to make sure budgets are reported in the correct currency.

Properties.Name: traversedpath
Properties.Description: For internal use only.

Properties.Name: utcconversiontimezonecode
Properties.Description: Time zone code that was in use when the record was created.

Properties.Name: versionnumber
Properties.Description: Version number of the phone call activity.
